  "prompt": "Which one is better: Royal Enfield Standard 350 or Classic 350?",
  "response": "Choosing between the Royal Enfield Standard 350 and the Classic 350 depends on your preferences and needs. Here's a comparison to help you decide:\n\n### Royal Enfield Standard 350\n**Pros:**\n- **Simplicity and Affordability:** The Standard 350 is often less expensive than the Classic 350, making it a more budget-friendly option.\n- **Basic Features:** It comes with fewer frills, which can be appealing if you prefer a no-nonsense, straightforward motorcycle.\n- **Lightweight:** Generally lighter than the Classic 350, which can make it easier to handle, especially for new riders.\n\n**Cons:**\n- **Minimalistic Design:** If you enjoy a more retro or vintage look, the Standard 350 might not satisfy your aesthetic preferences.\n- **Fewer Customization Options:** It typically comes with fewer accessories and customization options compared to the Classic 350.\n\n### Royal Enfield Classic 350\n**Pros:**\n- **Retro Styling:** The Classic 350 has a more vintage and appealing design that many riders find attractive.\n- **More Features:** It often comes with additional features and accessories, enhancing the overall riding experience.\n- **Customization:** More options for customization, allowing you to personalize your bike to your taste.\n\n**Cons:**\n- **Higher Cost:** Generally more expensive than the Standard 350.\n- **Heavier:** The added features and design elements can make it heavier, potentially impacting maneuverability.\n\n### Conclusion\n- **If you're on a budget and prefer a simple, no-frills motorcycle**, the **Standard 350** might be the better choice.\n- **If you value aesthetics, additional features, and customization options**, the **Classic 350** is likely the better option.\n\nUltimately, the best choice depends on your priorities regarding cost, style, features, and riding experience. It's a good idea to test ride both models to see which one feels right for you.",
